post_text:
Due to the impending inclement weather, Kenilworth Science and Technology School will remain closed for the remainder of this week. Missed instructional days of this week will be made up at the end of the school year in May. While virtual live class schedules will not be followed this week, teachers may post assignments on Schoology and on other KST virtual learning platforms for students to work on. Students will be able to work independently on these assignments at their own pace during this time and not be penalized if they are not able to complete assignments due to the effects of the storm.

Virtual live classes will continue on Monday, August 31 and students are to follow their schedules on the Kenilworth Success Portal. Food pick-up services will resume next Tuesday, September 1, 2020.

As always, the safety of students and employees is our top priority.

post_text:
Due to the threat of hurricanes Marco and Laura, Kenilworth Science and Technology school building will be closed including our front office, and ALL virtual live classes are canceled on Monday, August 24th and Tuesday, August 25th. However, teachers may post assignments on Schoology and on other KST virtual learning platforms for students to work on. Students will be able to work independently on these assignments at their own pace during this time and not be penalized if they are not able to complete assignments due to the effects of the storm.

These closures will also affect the prepared meals offered to families for pick-up on Tuesday's. Announcements will be made of when meal pick-ups will be rescheduled on Tuesday afternoon.

Additional updates will be provided on Tuesday afternoon as well.

Stay Safe!

post_text:
Dear Kenilworth Parents,

We are preparing for the 2020-21 school year, which is scheduled to begin on Thursday, August 6, 2020. Our commitment to you and your children has not changed: Our top priority is to create a safe environment in which children can learn and be successful. We need your assistance so we can complete our planning.

Each family will choose whether to continue learning from home or return to Kenilworth for on-campus learning for the 2020-2021 school year, based on each family’s needs.

We must hear from you as soon as possible so we can finalize our plans. Fill out our Back-To-School survey by July 6th. The survey can be reached at this link: https://tinyurl.com/KSTBacktoSchool2020

See the full letter here: https://www.kenilworthschool.org/news/recent-news/important-back-to-school-information-2020-2021-school-year

post_text:
Kenilworth Science and Technology School stands in solidarity with our community. We condemn the unjust and senseless killings of George Floyd, Ahmaud Arbery, Breonna Taylor and so many others and mourn the tragic loss of their lives. We raise our voices with our many community partners and call for the eradication of racist elements in our systems that have historically disempowered and disenfranchised black students.

Like our students, we strive for a world where we, our families, and our communities can live free of bigotry and discrimination and enjoy equality of opportunity. As a school, we believe education is a tool that all of us can use to bring about meaningful change in our country and in the world.

We will continue to work every day to serve our students, staff, families, and communities and to lift them up while we all stand up to systemic racism and injustice.

#Blacklivesmatter

Hasan Suzuk, M.Ed.
Executive Director

post_text:
Congrats to our student Sarah Patterson who finished in third place in the 2020 Louisiana State Science and Engineering Fair, which was staged as a virtual fair this year because of the coronavirus outbreak.

The state science fair, which is usually held on the LSU campus in Baton Rouge, is a competition among students who placed in one of regional fairs. Sara, whose project is called "Isoperimetric Inequality," finished in first place in mathematics in the Baton Rouge-area regional competition.
Judges performed online reviews of project research plans and abstracts, and winners were notified by email of the results over the weekend. Kenilworth was the only school in Baton Rouge to have a student place in the mathematics competition of the science fair.

The Scholastic Book Fair has started in the Kenilworth Library! We are excited to host this year's book fair from October 21st to October 25th in our school library. Students will have the opportunity to explore and purchase books from 7a.m.-5p.m. each day.

Did you know that if your child reads just 20 minutes per day they will be exposed to 1,800,000 words per year and will likely score better than 90% of their peers? So let's get excited about reading!

Hope to see you there!
text:
The Scholastic Book Fair has started in the Kenilworth Library! We are excited to host this year's book fair from October 21st to October 25th in our school library. Students will have the opportunity to explore and purchase books from 7a.m.-5p.m. each day.

Did you know that if your child reads just 20 minutes per day they will be exposed to 1,800,000 words per year and will likely score better than 90% of their peers? So let's get excited about reading!

Hope to see you there!

The students loved having them not only speak to them, but also participate!

Kenilworth's state report card shows impressive improvement

Kenilworth Science and Technology School posted an impressive 12 percent improvement in its School Performance Score in 2018, bringing its letter grade to a "C" under the scoring formula the Louisiana Department of Education has used for the last several years.

Click here for Details:
http://www.kenilworthschool.org/news/recent-news/kenilworths-state-report-card-shows-impressive-improvement

Registration is open for this year's Louisiana Elementary Math Olympiad at Kenilworth Science and Technology School!

The Olympiad will take place from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. on Saturday, November 10, at Kenilworth, 7600 Boone Drive in Baton Rouge. The event is free and open to all 5th-grade students in Louisiana who register at www.laemo.org. Any fifth-grade student attending any public, private, parochial, charter or home school in Louisiana is eligible to participate.

Click here to register!
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScMwL1Q_34sePrtj82gmz0Zo0eChNaGGLe82mcgg-DXPhU_8A/viewform
